---
import ElevationLayout from '../../layouts/ElevationLayout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/elevation/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../../components/elevation/Section.astro';
import { getProductBySlug } from '../../lib/products/registry';
import { productJsonLd } from '../../lib/structured-data';

const product = getProductBySlug('governance-score-card')!;
const jsonLd = productJsonLd(product, 'https://evoked.dev/products/governance-score-card');
---

<ElevationLayout
  title="Governance Score Card"
  description="Five questions. Five governance properties. Know what your score means and what to fix first. $1 PDF."
  structuredData={jsonLd}
>
  <Hero
    eyebrowParts={["Products", "Quick assessment"]}
    headline="What does your governance score mean?"
    metaphor={["Five questions. Five properties."]}
    sub="Know what to fix first."
  />

  <Section marker="FIG · I" heading="Why this exists">
    <p class="lede">
      Your agent system has five governance properties: Identity, Restraint,
      Accountability, Memory, and Charter. Each one is either present, partial,
      or missing. Do you know which?
    </p>
    <p class="pd-body">
      This card walks you through a quick self-assessment of all five properties,
      tells you what each gap means, what risk it carries, and one concrete action
      per finding. No theory. No fluff. Just the interpretation and the next step.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · II" heading="What you get">
    <div class="pd-features">
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Score interpretation grid</h3>
        <p>Each of the five governance properties mapped to FOUND, PARTIAL, or MISSING - with what each status actually means for your system.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>Risk assessment per gap</h3>
        <p>What happens when decision memory is missing? When refusal capability is absent? The risk isn't abstract - it's operational.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>One action per finding</h3>
        <p>Not a roadmap. Not a consulting pitch. One concrete next step per gap, completable in an afternoon.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-feature">
        <h3>EU AI Act context</h3>
        <p>Which governance gaps map to EU AI Act requirements. The use-based high-risk deadline is now 2 December 2027 under the May 2026 Digital Omnibus (provisional political agreement pending Official Journal publication). Article 5 prohibitions and General-Purpose AI rules are live today. The standards window is now.</p>
        <p class="pd-feature-fineprint"><em>Regulatory facts verified 2026-06-06.</em></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · III" heading="How it works">
    <div class="pd-pillars">
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">1</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Answer five questions</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">Does your agent have identity? Restraint? Accountability? Memory? A charter? Five yes-or-no questions. Two minutes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">2</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Score your system</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">Each property scores as FOUND, PARTIAL, or MISSING. Your governance posture in one page.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-pillar">
        <span class="pd-pillar-number">3</span>
        <div class="pd-pillar-body">
          <h3>Read the card</h3>
          <p class="pd-pillar-question">Match each result to the interpretation grid. Know the risk, know the fix, know the priority.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · IV" heading="Who this is for">
    <div class="pd-audience">
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Developers building agents</h3>
        <p>You shipped the agent. Now you want to know what governance looks like. Start with the five questions and the card.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Team leads evaluating risk</h3>
        <p>Run the scan on your team's agent projects. The card tells you which gaps to bring to the next standup.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pd-audience-card">
        <h3>Anyone curious about governance</h3>
        <p>A dollar. Five questions. A card. Five minutes of your time and you'll know more about agent governance than most conference talks teach.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="FIG · V" heading="Buy the score card">
    <div class="pd-purchase">
      <div class="pd-price">$1</div>
      <p class="pd-purchase-lead">PDF download. The interpretation guide for your governance scan.</p>
      <a
        href={product.stripePaymentLink}
        class="pd-buy-cta"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
      >Get the Score Card</a>
      <p class="pd-purchase-fineprint">
        The card includes the five-question self-assessment and the full
        interpretation guide. Two minutes to score, five minutes to understand.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section marker="NOTA · BENE" heading="Go deeper" closing={true}>
    <p class="lede">
      The score card tells you what's missing. If you want to build what's
      missing, two doorways from here.
    </p>
    <div class="pd-upsell">
      <a href="/products/governance-templates-guided" class="pd-upsell-card">
        <h3>Governance Templates ($5)</h3>
        <p>The five templates with filled-in examples from a real system. Charter, restraint, memory, deliberation, drift.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">View templates &rarr;</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/products/governance-implementation-guide" class="pd-upsell-card">
        <h3>Implementation Guide ($9.99)</h3>
        <p>Step-by-step for CrewAI, LangGraph, and Pydantic AI. From scan results to working governance.</p>
        <span class="pd-upsell-link">View guide &rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </Section>
</ElevationLayout>

<style>
  /* Page-local: feature-level fineprint for the verified-on
     date stamp under the EU AI Act feature. */
  .pd-feature-fineprint {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--el-text-quiet);
    margin-top: 0.5rem !important;
  }
</style>
